  "texts": [
    "The title-to-occupation list was curated from the SOC as described in 3.5.",
    "It contained 329 occupation titles in 11 occupation groups and can be used to map an occupation title (e.g.",
    "software developer) to an occupation (e.g.",
    "Computer and Math).",
    "We observed that among the 329 occupation titles, 293 of them could be unambiguously mapped to a unique occupation group using an unigram of the title, while 16 unigram titles were ambiguous and could be mapped to multiple occupation groups."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}